analog input pins
digital pins
0 - 5 volts
reset button
power led
TX/RX leds
atmega328p

analog pins A0 to A5 with anaogRead(), analogWrite()
digital pins gives 0 or 1 35 6 9 10 11 are pwm enabled pins
pwm eg. 60% duty cycle
power pins Vin

pin 13 LED : high means glow and not in low
power LED : connected to the power source
reset button
TX/RX LED : are to denote communication are connected to the 1st and 2nd pins used when using sensors
usb port powers the arduino also to upload code
Serial.println() prints on the serial monitor

pinMode(Pin No, Mode); to set as input or output
eg. pinMode(13,OUTPUT);
usually written in the setup function
digitalWrite(pin no, HIGH/LOW);
HIgh sets to 5V and 0V at low.
eg.
    pinMode(13, INPUT);
    digitalRead(13);

analogWrite(...)
analogRead(Pin_no); returns a 10 bit no. (0-1023)

TIME
delay(T), delayMicroseconds(T) where T is in milliseconds and microseconds respectively
micros(), millis() returns time since the arduino board began running the program
pulsein(Pin no, HIGH) gives the time in milliseconds from the time this command is initiated till Pin_no gives a HIGH pulse

SERIAL
used for serial ccommunication
Serial.begin(speed)

eg.
                //headers for eg, servo
int i=1;        //first variable declarations
void setup()
{
Serial.begin(9600)
}

void loop()
{
    Serial.println(i++);
    dekay(1000);
}

program flow -> first executes the setup()
                and then starts the loop infinitely

eg.
11 -> red 5 sec
12 -> orange 1.5 sec
13 -> green 5 sec
red,orange,green,orange,red,..

setup()
{
    pinMode(11,OUTPUT);
    pinMode(12,OUTPUT);
    pinMode(13,OUTPUT);
}
loop()
{
    digitalWrite(11,HIGH);
    delay(5000);
    digitalWrite(11,LOW);
    digitalWrite(12,HIGH);
    delay(1500);
    digitalWrite(12,LOW);
    digitalWrite(13,HIGH);
    delay(5000);
    digitalWrite(13,LOW);
    digitalWrite(12,HIGH);
    delay(1500);
    digitalWrite(12,LOW);
}

SENSORS

ultrasonic
one of the circles is a transmitter and the other is a receiver
has 4 pins one is VCC-5V and the ground
one is trig and the other is echo, trig will sends a pulse for 0 milliseconds

LCD

display certain info
GND,VCC,V0, used to control the contrast of the display, RS registor select, read/write, enable pin only when enable is hig hthe data is printed, 8 pins
D0-D7, anode, cathode; if anode high and cathode then can be used in the dark

lcd.begin(16,2); defines the size
lcd.clear(); clears the LCD
lcd.setCursor(n,m): moves the cursor to that array
LiquidCrystal lcd(12,,,,,);//(rs,en,d4,d5,d6,d7)

